                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 7: India has witnessed 1.31 lakh job losses during the April-June period, with textile, IT/BPO and gems and jewellery being the worst-affected sectors. According to a Labour Bureau survey, As regards the contract workers, there is an increase in employment by 0.40 lakh against a decline of 1.71 lakh in respect of direct employment.                            
	 Calcutta, Aug. 7: The deadlock between bank employees and Indian Banks Association has been resolved with the IBA agreeing to offer a 17.5 per cent wage hike and contribute 70 per cent of the Rs 6,000-crore that has to be created to accommodate employees who had opted for provident fund but want to join the pension scheme now.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 7: The economy is projected to grow at 6.5 per cent this fiscal, a survey conducted by the RBI said, revising the growth outlook upwards from 5.7 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 7: Sebi has asked asset management companies not to discriminate between mutual fund holders based on their amount of subscription while charging exit load.                                                                                                                           
